The paper deals with document layout understanding, which involves computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a methodology that involves transfer learning, which is a popular technique in machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI). Hence, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with object detection, which is a sub-field of CV and ML, and hence, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible sub-category.
